  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "If your Viber on PC is showing messages but not allowing you to reply, there might be several reasons for the issue. Here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot the problem:\n\n1. **Check Your Internet Connection**: Ensure that your PC is connected to the internet and that the connection is stable. You can do this by opening a web browser and visiting a website.\n\n2. **Restart Viber**: Close Viber completely and then restart it. This can resolve temporary issues with the application.\n\n3. **Log Out and Log Back In**: Try logging out of Viber on your PC and then logging back in to refresh your connection.\n\n4. **Update Viber**: Ensure that you have the latest version of Viber installed on your PC. Go to the Viber website or your app store and check for updates.\n\n5. **Check Firewall/Antivirus Settings**: Sometimes, firewall or antivirus software can interfere with Viber\u2019s connection. Make sure that Viber is allowed through your firewall.\n\n6. **Reconnect Your Viber Account**: If you are still having issues, try reconnecting your phone to Viber on your PC. Open Viber on your phone, go to \"More\" > \"Settings\" > \"Linked Devices,\" and ensure your PC is linked. You may unlink and relink if necessary.\n\n7. **Reinstall Viber**: As a last resort, you can uninstall Viber from your PC and then reinstall it. Make sure to back up any important messages or data if necessary.\n\n8. **Check Viber Status**: It\u2019s possible that there may be an issue with Viber's servers. You can check their official Twitter account or website to see if there are any ongoing service disruptions.\n\nIf you've tried all these steps and still can't send messages, you may want to contact Viber support for further assistance.",
